      "updated": 1778387127785,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "In a tree data structure, the total number of edges from root node to a particular node is called \nas DEPTH of that Node.",
      "fontSize": 26.228632271331033,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "In a tree data structure, the total number of edges from root node to a particular node is called \nas DEPTH of that Node.",
